title: Wall Street bull Ed Yardeni predicts stocks will fly 17% between now and 2021
text: Yardeni Research's Edward Yardeni believes the U.S. economy is picking up steam.

title: Here's what one top economist sees ahead for the Fed and US-China trade
text: Trade with China is the 'big unknown' for the Federal Reserve as it decides how best to support the U.S. economy, says Council on Foreign Relations Director of International Economies Benn Steil.

title: Why The Fed's Cuts May Be Working
text: After two cuts, the Fed's actions may be improving the prospects for the yield curve and producing more alignment between market expectations and policymakers.

title: 'Underdeveloped' warehousing in China could be an investing opportunity for property investors
text: China's e-commerce boom is fueling demand for storage spaces and offers opportunities for those looking into putting their money in real estate, says Jean Eric Salata from Baring Private Equity Asia.
